This course is for students at the upper elementary level of Japanese. The purpose of this course is to enable students to explain about themselves or to communicate with each other in simple Japanese. This course provides students with the knowledge of vocabularies, grammatical items, Kanji, and basic expressions for use in conversation through the exercises of speaking and writing about their own experiences and thoughts.

The goals of this course are same as Japanese Basic 3, which are listed below.

To be able to understand frequently used vocabularies and expressions on familiar topics and express one's own opinions and thoughts in simple Japanese.
To be able to describe familiar topics such as everyday life, one’s own experiences or wishes by using complex sentences in Japanese.
To be able to understand essential vocabularies or expressions frequently used in one’s own life and learn them in a proactive manner.
Students will be expected:

To be able to use a variety of expressions or vocabularies after reviewing all the contents taught in Japanese Basic 1 & 2 alongside of learning grammatical items and vocabularies taught in Japanese Basic 3.
To be able to form a useful basis for moving to an intermediate level of Japanese.
※ To achieve these listed above, students must take this course with “Japanese Basic 3”.

